  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Our working hypothesis is that reflectance confocal microscopy (RCM) can identify distinct
      subsets of melanocytic nevi that retain their distinctive pattern over time.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
